- "User activity" includes posts, replies, and likes;
- "Subscriptions" refer to forum subscriptions, and "active subscriptions" are those that are currently active;
- "Profile details" include first name, last name, bio, location, website, interests, and favorite topics.

- A "top contributor" is a user who has made the most replies in a specific topic within a forum;
- The query limits the results to the top 5 users across all forums;
- The forums are ordered by name, and within each forum, users are ordered by their reply count in descending order.

- A forum can have multiple topics;
- A topic can have multiple replies;
- The query ensures that even forums with no topics or replies are included in the results.

- "stars" refers to users in the social media context;
- "gathered the most admiration" refers to receiving the highest number of likes;
- "total number of likes on their topics and replies" includes likes from both the `topic_likes` and `reply_likes` tables;
- "shine in the constellation of user engagement" means being ranked by the total number of likes received.

- "Planted more than one seed of interest" refers to users with more than one forum subscription;
- "Number of seeds they've planted" refers to the total number of subscriptions;
- "Blossoms they've nurtured" refers to the total number of topics they've created;
- "Bees they've attracted" refers to the total number of replies they've received.

- "seeds of activity" refers to the total activities, posts, replies, and likes;
- "engagement" includes the total topics and replies viewed, and the total likes received for topics and replies;
- "community involvement" refers to the total subscriptions and active subscriptions;
- "personal garden plots" refers to the user profiles, where the completeness is measured by the number of profile fields filled and the total number of profile fields.

- "Top 5 most active users" refers to the users with the highest number of replies;
- "Last month" refers to the period from one month ago until now;
- "Activities" include any actions recorded in the `user_activity` table;
- "Replies" are counted from the `replies` table.

- "gardeners" refers to users on the platform;
- "blooming flowers" refers to topics created by users;
- "pollinators" refers to replies made by users;
- "admirers" refers to likes received by users;
- "rank in the community" refers to the activity rank based on the sum of topics, replies, and likes.

- "blossomed the most" refers to users with the highest number of activities;
- "from the first dawn to the last sunset of the year 2023" refers to the date range from '2023-01-01' to '2023-12-31';
- "petals" metaphorically represent the number of activities performed by each user.

- "Gardeners" refer to users;
- "Seeds" refer to posts;
- "Leaves" refer to replies;
- "Flowers" refer to likes;
- "Sunbeams" refer to views;
- "Plots" refer to forum subscriptions;
- "Badges" are awards given to users for their contributions.

- "Top 5 users" refers to the users ranked highest based on the number of likes received on their replies;
- "Replies" are comments or responses made by users in a forum or discussion board;
- "Likes" are positive reactions or upvotes given to the replies.

- "Engagement" refers to the level of interaction and participation of users in the platform, measured by topics created, views, likes, and replies;
- "Profile completeness" refers to the extent to which users have filled out their profile information, such as first name, last name, bio, location, website, interests, and favorite topics;
- "Roles" in a platform can include different user types such as member, moderator, admin, etc.;
- "Activity status" can indicate whether a user's account is active or inactive.

- "garden of achievements" refers to the platform or system where users earn badges and perform activities;
- "blooming flowers" are the badges earned by users;
- "active bees" are the activities performed by users;
- The year 2023 is the timeframe for the activities and badge earnings.
